::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:00.310 --> 00:00:03.180
Open up the borderless map, then

3
00:00:03.180 --> 00:00:06.380
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

4
00:00:06.380 --> 00:00:10.770
LET’S SAIL ON right now, hoist your sails up high

5
00:00:10.770 --> 00:00:13.760
Riding on the wind

6
00:00:18.890 --> 00:00:23.100
DON’T GIVE UP, it’s time to finish what we started

7
00:00:23.290 --> 00:00:26.070
So don't you grow disheartened

8
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.830
Laugh the tears away through the storm

9
00:00:30.030 --> 00:00:34.260
SHOUT IT OUT, when you feel down always remember

10
00:00:34.600 --> 00:00:36.860
That’s what your friends are there for

11
00:00:36.890 --> 00:00:39.020
Y’know there’s no point in fronting,

12
00:00:39.020 --> 00:00:42.940
your crew will always have your back

13
00:00:43.310 --> 00:00:47.040
Even in the face of utter darkness

14
00:00:47.270 --> 00:00:50.030
C’mon, BRAVE IT OUT We’ll be alright

15
00:00:50.330 --> 00:00:53.820
Together you know that we’ll never lose a fight

16
00:00:54.040 --> 00:00:56.810
Open up the borderless map, then

17
00:00:56.830 --> 00:00:59.670
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

18
00:00:59.970 --> 00:01:04.250
All great journeys starts with a single step

19
00:01:04.320 --> 00:01:05.260
DREAMIN’ ON

20
00:01:05.260 --> 00:01:08.040
Open up the borderless map, then

21
00:01:08.040 --> 00:01:10.780
Raise the flag we swore to defend

22
00:01:10.930 --> 00:01:13.670
We’ll never stop until we’ve reached the top

23
00:01:13.740 --> 00:01:18.140
Just be true to yourself until the end

24
00:01:18.270 --> 00:01:22.980
Set sail and grab it, DREAMIN ON

25
00:01:31.900 --> 00:01:34.450
<b>My Bible</b>

26
00:01:34.450 --> 00:01:36.700
Big Sis! Stay with me!

27
00:01:38.130 --> 00:01:39.120
Big Sis!

28
00:01:39.870 --> 00:01:41.580
Hey, dumbasses!

29
00:01:41.580 --> 00:01:43.580
Fetch the medics!

30
00:01:46.450 --> 00:01:47.170
Hey!

31
00:01:47.170 --> 00:01:47.940
Sir!

32
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:53.890
Find those two, corner them,
then summon the rest of us.

33
00:01:56.850 --> 00:01:59.200
Yamato, you bastard...

34
00:01:59.200 --> 00:02:00.850
Page One!

35
00:02:00.850 --> 00:02:03.510
You took a pretty nasty hit too.

36
00:02:04.490 --> 00:02:06.900
Yeah, that was quite the punch...

37
00:02:06.900 --> 00:02:08.850
Think he dislocated my jaw.

38
00:02:08.850 --> 00:02:10.230
That's all?!

39
00:02:10.650 --> 00:02:13.660
More importantly, where are the medics?

40
00:02:13.660 --> 00:02:15.910
We're here!

41
00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:29.130
You're hurting my eyes!

42
00:02:34.550 --> 00:02:36.760
Pay-Pay!

43
00:02:38.600 --> 00:02:40.560
It hurts ever so much!

44
00:02:40.560 --> 00:02:43.350
Poor sweet little me!

45
00:02:43.350 --> 00:02:45.560
Maybe you should pipe down then?

46
00:02:45.560 --> 00:02:47.390
What did you say?!

47
00:02:47.390 --> 00:02:49.230
Are you trying to make me cry?!

48
00:02:54.530 --> 00:02:56.900
That lousy Yamato!

49
00:02:56.900 --> 00:03:00.910
How dare he steal
Viceroy Kaido's Thunder Bagua?!

50
00:03:00.910 --> 00:03:02.500
She's fine all right.

51
00:03:03.670 --> 00:03:06.040
His is more like Blunder Bagua.

52
00:03:08.640 --> 00:03:12.140
It didn't even hurt...

53
00:03:12.140 --> 00:03:13.460
Big Sis...

54
00:03:13.460 --> 00:03:14.800
Master Page One!

55
00:03:14.800 --> 00:03:17.300
Young Master Yamato
and Straw Hat have stopped!

56
00:03:17.300 --> 00:03:18.340
Okay!

57
00:03:19.780 --> 00:03:21.430
Hey, Pay-Pay!

58
00:03:22.820 --> 00:03:25.810
Don't leave me!

59
00:03:28.600 --> 00:03:30.480
Where are you taking me?!

60
00:03:30.480 --> 00:03:33.070
I don't have time for strangers!

61
00:03:33.070 --> 00:03:34.490
Please wait.

62
00:03:34.490 --> 00:03:36.700
I merely wish to speak.

63
00:03:37.880 --> 00:03:39.440
Get out of my way!

64
00:03:53.770 --> 00:03:55.470
Listen to what I have to say!

65
00:04:09.980 --> 00:04:11.650
You have five seconds!

66
00:04:20.190 --> 00:04:21.620
People can hear us.

67
00:04:21.620 --> 00:04:23.160
Let's speak in private.

68
00:04:24.490 --> 00:04:26.000
Then forget it!

69
00:04:32.250 --> 00:04:34.210
Gum-Gum...

70
00:04:34.210 --> 00:04:36.420
Gatling!

71
00:04:52.090 --> 00:04:53.230
You stubborn jerk!

72
00:04:55.340 --> 00:04:57.690
Red Hawk!

73
00:05:06.820 --> 00:05:08.170
This reminds me of...

74
00:05:09.240 --> 00:05:11.670
my battle against him!

75
00:05:19.050 --> 00:05:20.300
Damn!

76
00:05:20.300 --> 00:05:21.430
They're gone!

77
00:05:21.430 --> 00:05:22.970
What's going on?

78
00:05:22.970 --> 00:05:24.300
Where's Yamato?

79
00:05:24.740 --> 00:05:25.720
I'm sorry!

80
00:05:25.720 --> 00:05:28.020
We lost them both!

81
00:05:29.730 --> 00:05:34.440
<b>Performance

Floor



Skull Dome</b>

82
00:05:35.190 --> 00:05:38.650
The day Kozuki Oden fell...

83
00:05:39.400 --> 00:05:43.910
his stronghold, Oden Castle,
fell alongside him!

84
00:05:44.710 --> 00:05:50.580
However, a group of people inside
the castle vanished into thin air!

85
00:05:51.100 --> 00:05:54.800
Samurai from the Red Scabbards
and this runt!

86
00:05:57.670 --> 00:06:00.550
Where did they disappear to?

87
00:06:02.220 --> 00:06:04.020
To the future!

88
00:06:05.190 --> 00:06:08.970
They crossed through twenty years of time...

89
00:06:08.970 --> 00:06:14.730
resurfacing in the Wano of today!
They haven't aged a day!

90
00:06:16.110 --> 00:06:19.900
And who exactly was responsible
for this sorcery?!

91
00:06:19.900 --> 00:06:22.150
I'll tell you...

92
00:06:22.150 --> 00:06:25.740
None other than Kozuki Toki!

93
00:06:26.280 --> 00:06:31.410
Oden's wife, Toki, was a witch who could
send these malcontents into the future!

94
00:06:35.570 --> 00:06:37.360
No way!

95
00:06:37.360 --> 00:06:41.880
There are brats with topknots all over Wano!

96
00:06:42.590 --> 00:06:46.090
The Kozuki name died out decades ago!

97
00:06:46.090 --> 00:06:47.760
Right, brother?!

98
00:06:51.390 --> 00:06:52.810
Yeah, man!

99
00:06:52.810 --> 00:06:54.850
Y-You're totally right!

100
00:06:57.020 --> 00:06:59.320
Yo, yo, Shogun Orochi!

101
00:06:59.320 --> 00:07:02.190
Don't keep him so far from us!

102
00:07:02.190 --> 00:07:04.650
Bring that brat down here!

103
00:07:04.650 --> 00:07:07.570
I wanna gouge his freakin' eyes out!

104
00:07:08.510 --> 00:07:10.870
How dare you call my mother a witch?!

105
00:07:10.870 --> 00:07:13.620
Y-You will pay for that, Orochi!

106
00:07:14.210 --> 00:07:18.040
Insolent whelp! Don't try to act tough!

107
00:07:18.040 --> 00:07:21.170
How should I execute you?!

108
00:07:21.170 --> 00:07:22.300
Impalement?

109
00:07:22.300 --> 00:07:23.210
Shooting?

110
00:07:23.210 --> 00:07:26.130
Or maybe boiling?!

111
00:07:27.090 --> 00:07:29.470
What should we do, Boss?

112
00:07:29.470 --> 00:07:31.720
I can't stand watching Momo like this!

113
00:07:31.720 --> 00:07:34.310
The samurai will surely act.

114
00:07:34.680 --> 00:07:37.400
Hold fast, Nico Robin!

115
00:07:38.310 --> 00:07:46.000
Lord Momonosuke!

116
00:07:47.840 --> 00:07:51.470
Though frustrated by their inability
to rescue Momonosuke,

117
00:07:51.470 --> 00:07:56.000
the raiding forces have successfully
blended into the banquet!

118
00:07:58.910 --> 00:08:04.790
Meanwhile, Law's submarine, the Polar Tang,
which was carrying the Red Scabbards samurai,

119
00:07:58.950 --> 00:08:00.450
<b>Law</b>

120
00:08:00.960 --> 00:08:06.460
<b>Law</b>

121
00:08:04.710 --> 00:08:04.920
<b>LawLaw</b>

122
00:08:04.790 --> 00:08:06.970
reached the back of the island.

123
00:08:06.460 --> 00:08:06.960
<b>Law</b>

124
00:08:10.850 --> 00:08:13.140
Adjust trim, 38 degrees!

125
00:08:13.510 --> 00:08:15.350
Adjusting, 38 degrees!

126
00:08:16.140 --> 00:08:18.550
Get as close to the island as possible!

127
00:08:18.550 --> 00:08:19.270
Yes, sir!

128
00:08:24.480 --> 00:08:28.070
Strong currents are forming all around us!

129
00:08:40.540 --> 00:08:42.290
It's the same up there.

130
00:08:42.290 --> 00:08:44.750
When we surface, we'll only get one shot!

131
00:08:44.750 --> 00:08:46.130
Understood!

132
00:08:46.530 --> 00:08:49.180
We're counting on you, Traffy!

133
00:08:49.650 --> 00:08:51.970
Bepo! Shachi! Penguin!

134
00:08:51.970 --> 00:08:53.180
Are you ready?!

135
00:08:53.180 --> 00:08:55.520
Aye, aye, Captain!

136
00:08:55.520 --> 00:08:57.020
– Aye, aye, sir!
– Aye, aye, sir!

137
00:08:57.020 --> 00:09:00.820
We're coming for you, Kaido!

138
00:09:02.310 --> 00:09:04.070
All systems clear!

139
00:09:04.070 --> 00:09:05.940
Ready to surface anytime!

140
00:09:07.690 --> 00:09:09.570
Alright! Surface!

141
00:09:32.350 --> 00:09:33.580
It's snowing...?

142
00:09:37.560 --> 00:09:38.680
Room!

143
00:09:54.200 --> 00:09:55.570
Shambles!

144
00:09:57.660 --> 00:09:58.740
They're gone!

145
00:10:00.540 --> 00:10:02.160
Close the door!

146
00:10:02.160 --> 00:10:03.710
We're resubmerging!

147
00:10:03.710 --> 00:10:04.670
Roger!

148
00:10:04.670 --> 00:10:06.450
Rapid descent!

149
00:10:15.260 --> 00:10:16.510
We're here!

150
00:10:16.930 --> 00:10:19.890
That technique of yours is remarkable!

151
00:10:21.760 --> 00:10:23.700
There are two entrances.

152
00:10:23.700 --> 00:10:26.270
No doubt Kaido will be up there.

153
00:10:27.900 --> 00:10:29.020
Hey!

154
00:10:29.020 --> 00:10:31.990
Can't you be a little more gentle?!

155
00:10:31.990 --> 00:10:33.280
You're asking too much!

156
00:10:33.280 --> 00:10:35.660
Whose great idea was this anyway?!

157
00:10:37.030 --> 00:10:38.580
Hey, wait!

158
00:10:39.290 --> 00:10:40.830
That must be...

159
00:10:54.770 --> 00:10:56.680
Ow, ow, ow...

160
00:10:56.680 --> 00:10:59.720
Come on, mew need to be careful!

161
00:10:59.720 --> 00:11:01.520
Nekomamushi!

162
00:11:01.520 --> 00:11:04.310
You have grown much bigger!

163
00:11:05.390 --> 00:11:08.020
Kawamatsu! You're alive!

164
00:11:09.190 --> 00:11:10.230
Ashura!

165
00:11:10.230 --> 00:11:11.980
You made it too!

166
00:11:11.980 --> 00:11:14.110
Yeah, it's been a while!

167
00:11:17.280 --> 00:11:20.280
Marco! You carried him here?!

168
00:11:21.370 --> 00:11:24.580
Carrying two people really takes it out of you!

169
00:11:24.960 --> 00:11:26.000
Two?!

170
00:11:37.700 --> 00:11:39.680
– Izo!
– Izo!

171
00:12:00.990 --> 00:12:02.370
Big Brother...

172
00:12:06.480 --> 00:12:10.380
Big Brother!

173
00:12:14.550 --> 00:12:17.930
Kiku, you have become a fine samurai.

174
00:12:17.930 --> 00:12:19.970
– Izo!
– Izo!

175
00:12:19.970 --> 00:12:22.220
You are a sight for sore eyes!

176
00:12:22.220 --> 00:12:24.180
I am so glad that you came back!

177
00:12:24.850 --> 00:12:28.350
I forgot to mention it before!

178
00:12:28.350 --> 00:12:33.550
Marco said he knew Izo's whereabouts,
so I went there to see him!

179
00:12:33.550 --> 00:12:36.400
Marco! You haven't changed one bit!

180
00:12:36.400 --> 00:12:37.570
You think?

181
00:12:37.570 --> 00:12:40.570
We can reminisce about
the good old days later!

182
00:12:41.820 --> 00:12:46.750
Something on the sea caught my eye earlier,
so I'm gonna go check it out.

183
00:12:50.120 --> 00:12:52.210
Marco! Thank you!

184
00:12:58.880 --> 00:13:01.680
I'm glad I waited for twenty years.

185
00:13:03.090 --> 00:13:06.310
Let's take down Kaido at any cost!

186
00:13:07.640 --> 00:13:10.230
Hey, is Linlin ready yet?!

187
00:13:10.230 --> 00:13:14.570
Oh, Emperor Big Mom is
already on her way here!

188
00:13:15.610 --> 00:13:18.490
You should've told me that, Bao Huang!

189
00:13:19.910 --> 00:13:21.360
My bad!

190
00:13:22.490 --> 00:13:24.240
You can go now.

191
00:13:24.990 --> 00:13:29.370
We'll make our grand announcement
alongside Momonosuke's execution!

192
00:13:30.370 --> 00:13:31.610
Let's go!

193
00:13:39.880 --> 00:13:41.220
All right!

194
00:13:41.220 --> 00:13:44.640
A toast to celebrate this execution!

195
00:13:47.060 --> 00:13:49.600
Oh, Viceroy Kaido?

196
00:14:03.700 --> 00:14:07.370
Here comes Viceroy Kaido!

197
00:14:16.130 --> 00:14:17.800
Listen up!

198
00:14:18.800 --> 00:14:20.460
All you bastards!

199
00:14:21.030 --> 00:14:26.260
Allow me to spice up this brat's dull execution.

200
00:14:29.430 --> 00:14:34.020
This is... the New Onigashima Project!

201
00:14:46.240 --> 00:14:53.370
<b>Castle

Attic</b>

202
00:14:57.030 --> 00:14:58.350
Five minutes!

203
00:15:01.800 --> 00:15:03.420
Years ago...

204
00:15:04.340 --> 00:15:05.500
I told my father...

205
00:15:06.740 --> 00:15:09.100
that I wanted to become Kozuki Oden.

206
00:15:10.100 --> 00:15:10.890
Huh?!

207
00:15:10.890 --> 00:15:13.430
In return, he disciplined me thoroughly.

208
00:15:13.430 --> 00:15:16.350
Why are you telling me this?!

209
00:15:16.350 --> 00:15:18.060
And why now of all times?!

210
00:15:18.760 --> 00:15:22.530
Twenty years ago,
I witnessed Oden's execution...

211
00:15:23.350 --> 00:15:25.110
the Legendary Hour.

212
00:15:26.720 --> 00:15:29.250
As a samurai, he was peerless.

213
00:15:30.220 --> 00:15:31.580
The ones who killed him...

214
00:15:32.240 --> 00:15:34.280
were Orochi and my father...

215
00:15:35.300 --> 00:15:36.670
Kaido!

216
00:15:37.880 --> 00:15:39.170
It was infuriating...!

217
00:15:39.840 --> 00:15:41.630
Yet, above all,

218
00:15:42.130 --> 00:15:45.470
my heart was stirred. My tears flowed freely!

219
00:15:47.840 --> 00:15:51.760
Later, I found this in Kuri.

220
00:15:54.140 --> 00:15:56.890
"Oden's Travel Record"

221
00:15:54.140 --> 00:15:57.100
Kozuki Oden's logbook.

222
00:15:57.640 --> 00:15:59.650
Oh, his journal!

223
00:16:02.900 --> 00:16:05.010
It's my bible!

224
00:16:06.110 --> 00:16:09.820
Not even my father or his crew
know about this journal!

225
00:16:09.820 --> 00:16:14.950
The pages are filled with his heroic tales
and other important tidbits.

226
00:16:15.500 --> 00:16:18.330
Now that the Red Scabbards are dead,

227
00:16:18.330 --> 00:16:20.780
someone has to inherit Oden's will!

228
00:16:22.170 --> 00:16:23.590
That's why...

229
00:16:25.500 --> 00:16:28.130
I'm going to open up this country!

230
00:16:45.740 --> 00:16:46.960
You're...

231
00:16:55.830 --> 00:16:58.620
Allow me to fight alongside you!

232
00:17:03.710 --> 00:17:06.800
You said you were Kaido's son.

233
00:17:08.910 --> 00:17:11.300
Kozuki Oden was a man, correct?

234
00:17:11.300 --> 00:17:13.850
So I became a man, too.

235
00:17:14.810 --> 00:17:17.390
You are incredibly strong.

236
00:17:17.390 --> 00:17:21.020
I could tell you were holding back
when we fought before.

237
00:17:28.280 --> 00:17:30.240
You remind me of Ace.

238
00:17:30.240 --> 00:17:31.320
Wha...?!

239
00:17:39.750 --> 00:17:40.960
Huh?!

240
00:17:41.750 --> 00:17:44.330
<b>Kaido's Daughter</b>

241
00:17:43.000 --> 00:17:44.370
<b>(Self-Proclaimed Kozuki Oden)</b>

242
00:17:44.130 --> 00:17:44.450
<b>Yam</b>

243
00:17:44.200 --> 00:17:44.370
<b>Ya</b>

244
00:17:44.250 --> 00:17:44.410
<b>Y a Kaido's Daughter m</b>

245
00:17:44.380 --> 00:17:44.630
<b>ato</b>

246
00:17:44.450 --> 00:17:44.540
<b>Yama</b>

247
00:17:44.540 --> 00:17:46.670
<b>Yamato</b>

248
00:17:51.090 --> 00:17:54.850
<b>Rear

Entrance</b>

249
00:18:11.170 --> 00:18:13.610
I knew you would come...

250
00:18:13.610 --> 00:18:18.830
There was no trace of
a samurai invasion...

251
00:18:18.830 --> 00:18:22.040
but I knew deep down that
you could never stay away.

252
00:18:24.170 --> 00:18:28.250
I know your tenacity better than anyone!

253
00:18:29.170 --> 00:18:31.130
They're really here!

254
00:18:31.130 --> 00:18:35.430
After hiding like rats
for twenty years since the boiling!

255
00:18:37.110 --> 00:18:38.350
Kanjuro...

256
00:18:38.350 --> 00:18:40.220
Have you betrayed us?!

257
00:18:40.680 --> 00:18:43.100
Your raid ends right here.

258
00:18:43.690 --> 00:18:48.570
Izo, you have returned...
just to fight this losing battle?

259
00:18:51.490 --> 00:18:53.950
They're decapitated, yet still able to fight...

260
00:18:54.530 --> 00:18:55.910
Nicely drawn.

261
00:18:55.910 --> 00:18:58.780
They look just like you guys, don't they?!

262
00:18:58.780 --> 00:19:04.120
With Oden, you lost your head, and yet
the body of the samurai writhes on.

263
00:19:04.120 --> 00:19:07.000
We still have our head!

264
00:19:07.000 --> 00:19:09.800
Our lord is Momonosuke!

265
00:19:09.800 --> 00:19:12.210
Is Lord Momonosuke okay?!

266
00:19:14.260 --> 00:19:18.100
I cannot say for certain...

267
00:19:18.430 --> 00:19:21.910
He was trying the best he could to escape.

268
00:19:24.520 --> 00:19:27.230
How can I get to Lord Orochi?!

269
00:19:38.990 --> 00:19:40.830
Halt!

270
00:19:47.420 --> 00:19:52.300
I refuse to remain a burden to them!

271
00:20:12.190 --> 00:20:14.230
What are you doing?

272
00:20:28.170 --> 00:20:30.000
If I let you get away...

273
00:20:31.590 --> 00:20:34.880
then I cannot fulfill my role!

274
00:20:39.130 --> 00:20:42.640
I only intended to knock him out...

275
00:20:42.640 --> 00:20:45.720
but I overdid it a little...

276
00:20:46.120 --> 00:20:49.730
Luckily, he clung on to life,

277
00:20:49.730 --> 00:20:53.060
so I was able to hand him over to Lord Orochi.

278
00:20:54.650 --> 00:20:56.190
Lord Momonosuke!

279
00:20:56.730 --> 00:21:03.160
Any minute now, Momonosuke will
be executed on stage for all to see!

280
00:21:05.080 --> 00:21:08.840
All we have to do is stop you right here.

281
00:21:08.840 --> 00:21:12.630
Minutes from now, the history of
the Kozuki clan will come to an end.

282
00:21:12.630 --> 00:21:15.300
Don't mess with us, Kanjuro!

283
00:21:16.090 --> 00:21:18.260
Advance!

284
00:21:29.560 --> 00:21:30.850
Kappa Style:

285
00:21:33.100 --> 00:21:34.530
Yorikiri!

286
00:21:36.020 --> 00:21:38.190
Flower Shuriken!

287
00:21:48.960 --> 00:21:51.330
Go to hell!

288
00:21:57.460 --> 00:21:59.840
You-gara! What happened to your leg?!

289
00:22:01.810 --> 00:22:03.010
It's my two-sword style!

290
00:22:03.010 --> 00:22:04.180
Isn't it cool?

291
00:22:04.180 --> 00:22:05.510
It's purrific!

292
00:22:05.510 --> 00:22:06.600
Now what is that?

293
00:22:06.600 --> 00:22:07.600
Isn't it cool?

294
00:22:07.600 --> 00:22:11.600
This will tear Kaido to shreds!

295
00:22:11.600 --> 00:22:12.940
Cool...

296
00:22:18.980 --> 00:22:21.110
What's wrong, Kiku?

297
00:22:21.110 --> 00:22:24.450
More... Cry some more!

298
00:22:25.120 --> 00:22:26.240
Come on...

299
00:22:26.870 --> 00:22:28.450
Come on...

300
00:22:28.450 --> 00:22:29.830
Come on!

301
00:22:36.330 --> 00:22:40.170
Please cease your drivel, Kanjuro.

302
00:22:43.890 --> 00:22:47.180
To me, Kanjuro of the Evening Shower...

303
00:22:48.340 --> 00:22:50.270
was a precious friend.

304
00:22:54.260 --> 00:22:56.160
Prepare yourself.

305
00:22:56.160 --> 00:22:59.900
The wounds from this blade
shall follow you to your grave.

306
00:23:00.030 --> 00:23:07.820
<b>Kikunojo of the Lingering Snow
A Retainer of the Kozuki Clan</b>

307
00:23:00.690 --> 00:23:05.980
Like the snow that remains in spring, so, too,
shall they torment your soul forevermore!

308
00:23:11.660 --> 00:23:12.870
Come at me, Kiku!

309
00:23:27.510 --> 00:23:30.640
Hey! Turn on the video
transponder snail already!

310
00:23:30.640 --> 00:23:33.730
Kaido's speech has started!

311
00:23:34.600 --> 00:23:37.850
I, as Kozuki Oden, thought that you...

312
00:23:37.850 --> 00:23:43.530
as Ace's brother, would allow me
to board your ship, so I gathered info on you.

313
00:23:43.530 --> 00:23:44.530
Hey!

314
00:23:44.530 --> 00:23:47.530
Everyone loves Kozuki Oden!

315
00:23:47.530 --> 00:23:50.160
You can't just be him!

316
00:23:51.200 --> 00:23:53.540
Fine, you're more Oden than I am!

317
00:23:53.540 --> 00:23:56.120
What do you mean I'm more Oden than you?!

318
00:23:57.420 --> 00:24:00.340
Even if I am Oden, I'm still not free...

319
00:24:02.190 --> 00:24:03.960
because of these cuffs!

320
00:24:07.090 --> 00:24:10.500
I wanted to set out to sea
along with Ace and his crew...

321
00:24:13.140 --> 00:24:17.690
but I've been held captive
on this island since I was eight!

322
00:24:19.600 --> 00:24:21.310
Aren't those for prisoners?

323
00:24:21.310 --> 00:24:22.690
Yes!

324
00:24:22.690 --> 00:24:26.780
My father said they would explode
should I ever leave the island.

325
00:24:27.320 --> 00:24:31.200
Honestly, I think that was probably a lie...

326
00:24:31.200 --> 00:24:34.160
because what kind of a parent
would blow up their own son?!

327
00:24:34.990 --> 00:24:39.170
But when I think of the worst case scenario,
I feel weak at the knees...

328
00:24:39.170 --> 00:24:41.420
because my father is that kind of man.

329
00:24:41.420 --> 00:24:43.170
Want me to take them off?

330
00:24:44.130 --> 00:24:45.010
What?!

331
00:24:45.010 --> 00:24:49.680
Do you really wanna fight alongside us?

332
00:24:49.680 --> 00:24:53.760
If you come with me, I'll be kicking
Kaido's ass right in front of you!

333
00:24:53.760 --> 00:24:56.020
I wish I could do it myself!

334
00:24:56.020 --> 00:25:00.650
I've lost count of the beatings
he's given me since I was a child!

335
00:25:00.650 --> 00:25:03.570
Every time I challenged him, I was defeated!

336
00:25:03.570 --> 00:25:04.570
I see.

337
00:25:04.570 --> 00:25:06.220
Okay, I'll take them off for you!

338
00:25:06.220 --> 00:25:07.740
Take them off?

339
00:25:07.740 --> 00:25:10.820
They've restricted my freedom
for twenty years...

340
00:25:10.820 --> 00:25:12.950
It's not as easy as...

341
00:25:12.950 --> 00:25:16.310
It's been two years since
the Summit War against Whitebeard!

342
00:25:22.130 --> 00:25:25.010
It's footage from the Performance Floor!

343
00:25:27.070 --> 00:25:30.430
The gears of the world are turning once again!

344
00:25:30.430 --> 00:25:35.510
The abolition of the Seven Warlords wasn't
some act of madness by the government!

345
00:25:40.600 --> 00:25:43.350
It's a sign of confidence in their ability

346
00:25:43.350 --> 00:25:47.440
to bring us to heel with new
countermeasures at Marine Headquarters.

347
00:25:51.450 --> 00:25:56.280
But while the World Government
wallows in ignorance,

348
00:25:56.860 --> 00:26:00.020
we will gather the most
powerful forces in this world...

349
00:26:00.020 --> 00:26:02.620
the ancient weapons!

350
00:26:08.170 --> 00:26:10.300
To accomplish that...

351
00:26:19.470 --> 00:26:22.440
we have entered into
an alliance with Big Mom!

352
00:26:38.160 --> 00:26:40.040
Did I hear you...

353
00:26:40.330 --> 00:26:46.670
<b>Olin the Oiran
Captain of the Big Mom Pirates
Bounty: 4 Billion 388 Million Berries</b>

354
00:26:41.160 --> 00:26:44.720
call out my name, Kaido?

355
00:26:53.340 --> 00:26:54.660
Oh, my...

356
00:26:55.510 --> 00:26:56.890
Big Mom?!

357
00:26:59.890 --> 00:27:03.090
Welcome back, Zeus.

358
00:27:03.100 --> 00:27:05.430
Ma... ma...

359
00:27:05.430 --> 00:27:06.230
Mama!

360
00:27:09.610 --> 00:27:12.780
She's terrifying up close!

361
00:27:12.780 --> 00:27:15.610
She's the world's strongest old hag!

362
00:27:20.580 --> 00:27:21.830
Zeus!

363
00:27:22.980 --> 00:27:23.620
Nami!

364
00:27:24.040 --> 00:27:25.670
They were caught?!

365
00:27:27.170 --> 00:27:30.380
You're finally here, Linlin!

366
00:27:30.380 --> 00:27:33.010
What took you so long?!

367
00:27:33.600 --> 00:27:36.840
Don't be such a stickler, Kaido!

368
00:27:36.840 --> 00:27:38.850
I made it in time.

369
00:27:44.180 --> 00:27:46.730
As Kaido said,

370
00:27:46.730 --> 00:27:51.570
we formed an alliance with a purpose in mind!

371
00:27:52.440 --> 00:27:53.690
A purpose?

372
00:27:53.690 --> 00:27:57.030
If we're at each other's throats,
it's out of our reach,

373
00:27:57.030 --> 00:28:00.660
but if we join hands,
it's already within our grasp!

374
00:28:00.660 --> 00:28:02.830
Listen up, you louts!

375
00:28:02.830 --> 00:28:06.460
We're doubling down on piracy!

376
00:28:06.460 --> 00:28:08.670
At long last...

377
00:28:08.670 --> 00:28:11.460
...we're going to claim...

378
00:28:14.090 --> 00:28:17.260
...the great treasure
One Piece!

379
00:28:24.020 --> 00:28:25.390
The One Piece...

380
00:28:25.840 --> 00:28:28.900
What the heck! That's my treasure!

381
00:28:28.900 --> 00:28:31.060
Those jerks!

382
00:28:32.730 --> 00:28:35.740
The fear of the ancient weapons...

383
00:28:35.740 --> 00:28:39.640
will ignite a terrible war across the world!

384
00:28:40.490 --> 00:28:42.490
Prepare yourselves!

385
00:28:42.490 --> 00:28:47.960
That is the violent world that we desire!

386
00:28:54.460 --> 00:28:56.300
How exciting!

387
00:28:58.360 --> 00:29:02.470
Any of you who serve Orochi, listen up!

388
00:29:03.510 --> 00:29:06.470
You've got a choice to make.

389
00:29:08.560 --> 00:29:10.480
A choice?

390
00:29:11.480 --> 00:29:13.440
This country...

391
00:29:13.440 --> 00:29:16.030
is a natural stronghold surrounded by the falls,

392
00:29:16.030 --> 00:29:21.610
which makes it difficult for the Marines
and the World Government to penetrate.

393
00:29:21.610 --> 00:29:24.410
If we build more weapons factories...

394
00:29:26.350 --> 00:29:30.040
and force even the people
of the Flower Capital to work,

395
00:29:30.040 --> 00:29:36.000
this place will become a lawless land,
a paradise for pirates!

396
00:29:41.630 --> 00:29:42.920
Hey...

397
00:29:45.510 --> 00:29:46.560
Hey!

398
00:29:46.950 --> 00:29:49.930
Kaido, you swine!

399
00:29:49.930 --> 00:29:53.060
The Flower Capital is my territory!

400
00:29:57.900 --> 00:29:59.860
Do you hear me?!

401
00:30:01.120 --> 00:30:06.990
For torturing the Kurozumi Clan,
I'll bring those Kozuki devils to their knees

402
00:30:06.990 --> 00:30:12.920
and subject them to all manner of horrors
to keep them from rising up!

403
00:30:12.920 --> 00:30:17.920
Forever and ever!

404
00:30:17.920 --> 00:30:21.010
Wano is mine to destroy!

405
00:30:21.010 --> 00:30:24.660
This country belongs to me!

406
00:30:24.660 --> 00:30:28.430
Know your place, Kaido!

407
00:30:28.430 --> 00:30:30.890
You're not even from here!

408
00:30:30.890 --> 00:30:36.610
Who do you think is making it possible
for you to procure weapons?!

409
00:30:36.610 --> 00:30:39.070
Wano can only exist with me!

410
00:30:39.070 --> 00:30:41.030
Don't you dare forget that!

411
00:30:46.340 --> 00:30:48.450
I see you understand.

412
00:30:48.880 --> 00:30:50.660
What we've got to do now...

413
00:30:50.660 --> 00:30:53.460
is kill that brat immedia–

414
00:31:09.550 --> 00:31:11.140
I don't care!

415
00:31:11.140 --> 00:31:13.850
We don't need him anymore!

416
00:31:35.920 --> 00:31:37.630
Utter tripe!

417
00:31:42.150 --> 00:31:44.010
To me...

418
00:31:48.800 --> 00:31:50.470
both the Kurozumi Clan...

419
00:31:51.220 --> 00:31:53.100
and the Kozuki Clan...

420
00:31:56.190 --> 00:31:58.980
mean nothing!

421
00:32:11.240 --> 00:32:11.870
Momo!

422
00:32:12.380 --> 00:32:14.290
Hey, that's Momo!

423
00:32:15.200 --> 00:32:17.080
Momo, wait for me!

424
00:32:17.080 --> 00:32:18.710
Hey, keep it down!

425
00:32:24.000 --> 00:32:25.260
Hey, what the hell?!

426
00:32:25.260 --> 00:32:26.760
What's going on?!

427
00:32:26.760 --> 00:32:27.930
Huh?

428
00:32:28.930 --> 00:32:32.470
And now the pirate-loving fly is dead.

429
00:32:32.470 --> 00:32:37.060
Those loyal to Orochi
have five seconds to decide!

430
00:32:37.820 --> 00:32:41.020
Become pirates and follow me...

431
00:32:41.410 --> 00:32:44.730
or challenge us right here and die?

432
00:32:45.400 --> 00:32:49.260
To prepare for the coming worldwide war,

433
00:32:49.260 --> 00:32:53.780
I will turn this country into a pirate empire!

434
00:32:55.620 --> 00:32:59.290
We'll ramp up the expeditions
for our primary business.

435
00:33:00.040 --> 00:33:01.000
So tonight,

436
00:33:01.000 --> 00:33:04.380
we will relocate Onigashima
to the Flower Capital,

437
00:33:04.380 --> 00:33:06.670
and Wano will fall!

438
00:33:07.300 --> 00:33:09.010
That bastard!

439
00:33:09.010 --> 00:33:12.760
The country's name will be New Onigashima!

440
00:33:12.760 --> 00:33:15.890
And the new shogun will be my son...

441
00:33:15.890 --> 00:33:17.600
Yamato!

442
00:33:21.060 --> 00:33:22.240
What did he...

443
00:33:23.690 --> 00:33:27.650
just say?!

444
00:33:34.150 --> 00:33:36.540
You can't just force that on me!

445
00:33:36.540 --> 00:33:38.830
You shitty old man!

446
00:33:39.410 --> 00:33:40.330
Hurry up!

447
00:33:40.330 --> 00:33:42.030
They're gonna kill Momo!

448
00:33:42.030 --> 00:33:43.800
I know a shortcut!

449
00:33:43.800 --> 00:33:44.540
Okay!
